### Test Trading API Endpoints
### Use this file with VS Code REST Client extension or similar

### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/v1

### 1. Get all available assets
GET {{baseUrl}}/trading/assets/available

###

### 2. Get available stocks only
GET {{baseUrl}}/trading/assets/available/type/STOCK

###

### 3. Search for assets
GET {{baseUrl}}/trading/assets/available/search?query=apple

###

### 4. Check client wallet (assuming client ID 1 exists)
GET {{baseUrl}}/trading/wallet/1

###

### 5. Add funds to wallet
POST {{baseUrl}}/trading/wallet/1/deposit?amount=10000

###

### 6. Check wallet balance after adding funds
GET {{baseUrl}}/trading/wallet/1

###

### 7. Buy Apple stock
POST {{baseUrl}}/trading/buy?clientId=1&symbol=AAPL&quantity=10&price=175.50

###

### 8. Buy Bitcoin
POST {{baseUrl}}/trading/buy?clientId=1&symbol=BTC&quantity=0.1&price=43250

###

### 9. Check wallet balance after purchases
GET {{baseUrl}}/trading/wallet/1

###

### 10. Check if client has sufficient funds for a large purchase
GET {{baseUrl}}/trading/wallet/1/check?amount=50000

###

### 11. Try to buy with insufficient funds (should fail)
POST {{baseUrl}}/trading/buy?clientId=1&symbol=TSLA&quantity=100&price=245.80

###

### 12. Get client's assets to verify purchases
GET {{baseUrl}}/assets/client/1

###

### 13. Get transactions for the first asset (you'll need to replace ID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/assets/1/transactions
